  "prompt": "Why does WiFi turn on in airplane mode?",
  "response": "WiFi can be turned on even when an electronic device is in airplane mode because airplane mode primarily disables cellular network connections to meet aviation safety regulations. However, it often still allows other wireless functions such as WiFi and Bluetooth to operate. This enables passengers to use inflight WiFi services offered by many airlines or to use Bluetooth for wireless headsets and other devices, all while complying with regulations that prevent interference with the plane\u2019s communication and navigation systems.",
